- cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the computation of rational function decomposition using Darboux polynomials, which is a topic related to symbolic computation.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also likely as the paper discusses the complexity of the proposed recombination strategy.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper presents an algorithm for rational function decomposition.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper mentions the use of the proposed algorithm in the sparse bivariate case, which is related to control systems.
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with the computation of polynomial factors, which can be related to computational geometry.
